Added config flags:
ASSISTANT_MODE = "ultra"
WAKE_FREE_MEDIA_CONTROLS = True
Restarted Leha. It is running as process 26216.
How Siri/Alexa work, simplified:

Wake trigger first: Apple says “Hey Siri” uses a tiny always-running recognizer before the rest of Siri handles the command. Source: https://machinelearning.apple.com/research/hey-siri
Session window: Siri supports follow-up requests after activation. Source: https://support.apple.com/guide/iphone/turn-on-and-activate-siri-iph83aad8922/ios
Alexa supports wake word and push/tap-to-talk invocation, with visible/listening/thinking/speaking states. Source: https://developer.amazon.com/en-US/docs/alexa/alexa-auto/invoking-alexa.html
Alexa-style skills are intent handlers: spoken request -> intent -> action/service -> spoken response. Source: https://developer.amazon.com/en-US/alexa/alexa-skills-kit/key-terms
Leha now follows that shape more closely:

wake/listen -> local reflex intents -> brain if needed -> tool/action -> speech
Try this:

Leha play Ilayaraja music Telugu
While music is playing:

stop
or:

pause
The remaining hard part for true Siri/Alexa-level behavior is acoustic echo cancellation. If YouTube is loud through speakers, the mic may still hear more music than your voice. The best fix is headset mic, lower speaker volume, or adding a real wake-word/AEC engine later.


